

sampling other images | March/24/2023 09:57:47
When in a math expression, use the following syntax to get the pixel value at given coordinates:

	i(#<image_index>,x,y,z,c,interpolation_type,boundary_conditions)

If we want to get the pixel value at (100,50) of image 2:
	i(#2,100,50)

Getting values of an image | April/02/2023 08:50:48
By using:
	{is#2}

You get the sum of the image at second index

naming command values | April/02/2023 16:31:11
Alright, if you want to name the arguments of your custom functions, use this:
	some_name=$1
This aliases the first argument with the name "some_name"